The South African Government, led by the Minister of Mineral Resources and Energy (DMRE), Gwede Mantashe is participating at the Annual Prospectors and Developers Association of Canada (PDAC) Trade and Conference show in Toronto, Canada. Minister Mantashe will deliver a keynote address during the South African Mining Investment Seminar under the theme “Accelerate investment through innovation.” Minister Mantashe will be supported by the Department of Trade and Industry, the South African Council for Geoscience, Mine Health and Safety Council, South African Diamond and Precious Metals Regulator and MINTEK. Read: Mantashe calls for more exploration The seminar aims to reaffirm South Africa’s commitment
to growing and sustaining the mining industry, and further confirm the country
as a favourable investment destination. South African Mining Investment Seminar Date: 2 March 2020 Venue: Metro Toronto Convention Center, North Building Presentation Room 202 Time: 09h00 – 11h00 Baker McKenzie Seminar Date: 2 March 2020 Venue: Metro Toronto Convention Centre, Room 104 C Time: 16:00 – 17:30 Presentation on recent developments and opportunities in the South African mineral sector Date: 3 March 2020 Venue: Fasken Martineau Du Moulin LLP, 333 Bay Street, Suite 2400, Toronto M5H2T6 Time: 16h30 – 18h00